On Friday, October 03, 2003, at 12:16PM, Jason Z Upper <jzupper(-at-)hotmail.com> wrote:

>The part I'm referring to looks like a clip that fits on the rear (RIR) of 
>the brake caliper.  It's shaped like a plus sign with the vertical part 
>going between the "rods" (bolts? pins?) that hold the pads and the 
>horizontal part going between the pads, presumably to hold them steady and 
>keep them, from rattling.
>
>Bentley calls them "rattle clips," but I don;t know if that's what they're 
>listed as...

It's called the spreader spring and the ATE style is 211-615-269A on a 73-79 bus.

Pick up 4 new retaining pins for both sides (ATE style 211-615-261A) so the spring has a smooth surface to slide on.

